<br>
While my beggar story starts out like most any other, it ends with an odd twist.  <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :hat --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/pimp.gif ALT=":hat"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~`<br>
<br>
<br>
After doing some smithing for the guild, I went to out into the yard in Freeport to aid someone who needed a bind.  I was a wee bit tipsy after drinking whatever beer I had left that my warrior friend Ephany hadn't drank.   In this case, I had *cough*  &quot;forgotten&quot; to give her a whole stack of twenty.  I kept swaying, and getting interrupted.   After casting a sucessful root upon myself, I bound him.  Then another  young chap walks up to me and asks, &quot;Pardon M'lady, have you any coin to spare for a poor wretch?&quot;  <br>
<br>
Well, the money I did have left, belonged to a guild member to smith his fine plate, and it was not mine to give.  I had spent my own money on hafling pickles for the mighty warrior Ephany, and more beer (and buying those outrageously priced periodots and jasper for buffs).<br>
<br>
I relayed as much to him, and I cast a spell to make him resolute and set the favors of the gods upon him.  I expected to hear some scorning from this guy or the typical, &quot;Thx&quot; and he'd dissappear.  Nope.<br>
<br>
He just said, &quot;M'lady, I thank you for your kindness, but these buffs will do me no good.&quot;  <br>
<br>
&quot;Why not?&quot; I pointed outside to the yard.  &quot;You can surely conquer anything in the yard now, and collect the items to earn a decent living for your age&quot;.<br>
<br>
&quot;I am merely a weak beggar, and these buffs will surely be wasted, as I will not be doing any combat today.&quot;<br>
<br>
<br>
&quot;You won't--  What?!&quot; I frowned.<br>
<br>
By now, some people were gathering around and they started ridiculing the guy.  It was getting interesting.<br>
<br>
&quot;As I said milady, I know nothing of life but begging here at these gates where me mum left me as a baby.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh, who was your mum and dad?&quot;  I asked.<br>
<br>
&quot;They were great people,&quot; he began to explain, &quot;They were killed by the evil dark elf sourcerers.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Ahh..  my sympathies,&quot; I said.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes, he said, my parent's were sent to battle the evil witch Najena.  They were slain.  My father's army sent me to this city on the back of a wolf.  <br>
<br>
I protested, &quot;Hey! I thought your mum dropped you off here!&quot; <br>
<br>
&quot;That wolf, she was the only mum I ever knew, m'lady.  She kept me warm and safe from harm in the forest, but she can teach me nothing of living in a cold mean city such as this one&quot;<br>
<br>
Now the ridiculers stopped poking fun at him, and were gathered around listening to his story and asking him questions.<br>
<br>
I gave him four of Ephany's halfling pickles and beers.  I figured Eph wouldn't miss them, besides feeding a barbarian too any pickles and beers can be dangerous, especially in the closed quarters of certain dungeons where the dungeon's interior decorator fancies torches and burning lava.<br>
<br>
Needless to say, I bid him farewell BEFORE he started to eat the pickles and drink the beer, because there is a campfire over near Boomba the pickle salesman.<br>
<br>
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
<br>
(yet another ooc note) I was really tired and had to take my leave for the night, but as the campout countdown scrolled up my screen...  I got a tell from him thanking me for the fun roleplaying, and that he was now going to go back to playing his main character on his regular server.  He gave me his main's name and the server name, and told me to say hi if I made a character on there.  Out of boredom of leveling his main, he had made the newbie just to roleplay a beggar.  What a hoot. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    Have you ever seen such a thing?<br>
