<br>
I have a story too, but its not about begging.  About roleplaying rather and how it can get a little carried away...<br>
<br>
----------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Being a young enchanter of level 23, I had just recently gotten my Iksar Illusion spell and was eager to try it out.  So what do I do? I head to South Karanas with my good friend Xorshaik (who was at the time a level 25 iksar monk), and Honeysong's necro Slithas (a level 20 iksar necro).<br>
<br>
I slap Iksar Illusion on myself and the 3 of us go parading around South Karanas praising Cazic Thule and repeatedly bashing Tunare.  We went so far as to kill one of the druids in NK so that I could loot some Wood Elf parts, which I to this day still show to various wood elf druids before I smile at them and announce I shall kill them.<br>
<br>
After about 30 minutes of Tunare bashing, some druid finally had enough.  She wa sick of being called a soft skin and a follower of a weak goddess.  So, the followers of Cazic Thule were challeneged to a duel against the followers of Tunare.  To be held in the arena.<br>
<br>
So the 3 of us traipse off to Arena, picking up a level 40 iksar warrior along the way, and shortly after we are surprised to find ourselves facing a few druids, a paladin, and a cleric (all elven, all followers of Tunare).<br>
<br>
Round 1.  I immediately make one of them my pet and sick them on their team mates using charm.  The necro pet takes out one of them, and the monks do their monkly amounts of damage.<br>
<br>
Cazic Thule 1, Tunare 0<br>
<br>
Round 2.  Charm has been disallowed.  Okay, thats not a problem.  Fear.  Wonderful pathing bug in Arena.  THe feared victim runs to the very centre of the stone platform and stands there as if rooted.<br>
<br>
Cazic Thule 2, Tunare 0<br>
<br>
Round 3.  Bit of solo action.  I think it was 25 monk vs 25 druid.  Xort lost.  He got kited. :(<br>
<br>
Cazic Thule 2, Tunare 1.<br>
<br>
This went on for a bit longer and the final score ended up being CT 4, Tunare 1.<br>
<br>
I think we all had a great time, no matter how many times Tunare got her butt whooped.  And to think, it was all started by a little roleplaying.<br>
<br>
-Trem<br>
